[SN]TITLE[SN]
Michael McKevitt: Irish Times says TDs back Real IRA chief release bid

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Five Irish MPs are supporting the family of Real IRA leader Michael McKevitt as they seek his release from prison while recovering from surgery, the Irish Times is reporting.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
McKevitt of Beech Park, Blackrock in County Louth, was convicted in 2003 of directing terrorism.
He was sentenced to 20 years in prison.
